.TH SSHKNOCK 1 "" "sshknockd 0.1.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
sshknock \- optional helper client for sending an SSHKnock sequence
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B sshknock
[\fB--config\fR \fIPATH\fR] \fBknock\fR \fISERVER\fR
.br
.B sshknock
[\fB--config\fR \fIPATH\fR] \fBssh\fR \fISERVER\fR [\fISSH_ARGS\fR...]
.br
.B sshknock
[\fB--config\fR \fIPATH\fR] \fBprint-script\fR \fISERVER\fR
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B sshknock
is an optional helper for sending the configured TCP or UDP knock sequence before connecting to SSH.
.PP
The required product flow remains clientless and can be performed with common tools such as nc or shell redirection.
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B knock
Sends the configured knock sequence to the server.
.TP
.B ssh
Sends the configured knock sequence, waits briefly, then runs ssh with the configured port.
.TP
.B print-script
Prints shell commands that reproduce the configured sequence without the helper binary.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I sshknock.toml
Default helper configuration path when no explicit config is provided.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR sshknockd (8),
.BR ssh (1),
.BR nc (1)
